Quoted By: >>15023583 >>15023789 >>15024022 >>15028407
>>15022697
Anyone who's read what I've done knows I have the little breeding pill. Normally it's an almost zero percent chance to crossbreed, the pill makes the female's eggs universally accepting of donor DNA. This is borrowed from an ancient (but still running) webcomic I read called 21st Century Fox. It's a lot more convoleted in the webcomic and involves some techno-jargon, but the basis is that cross breed DNA is given default species characteristics and then the father's DNA does its part of filling in the miscellaneous bits. Things like eye color, hair(some fur) color, and other small touches.

I've never gone into it because I keep my world building mostly 1) in my head and 2) in a real life journal. But there are things I've mentioned of my headcanon that I'm just not pointing out because it's just really autistic sounding when I type it up. Outside of the now defunct Pactbearer, all of my stories take place in the same world and follow the same rules. One of these rules, and this is a slight Femme Fatale spoiler that is seriously won't be relevant at all, is that several hair colors are not present in most 100% pure anthros. Things like blondes and strong reds just don't happen. So I'll save you the time of digging through pastebin to re-check Ariannis's hair color; somewhere along her family tree is a very much blonde hair blue eyed human. Some men strayed from the path during the crusades and got liberal with their taste in whores.
Hell, just having fur/head hair is indicative of mixed breeding in one's family tree (that'll be relevant -eventually-), but it's very hard to get out even with an insistent eugenics program/philosophy. So if great x10 uncle Grug Grug got it on with Shehasha the Sabertooth behind the waterfall, her descendants will be dealing with that shit while trying to put on their gas masks in the trenches of WW1. Most people don't care about this in the 21st century, some care -A LOT-. Everyone knows how that kind of song and dance goes.
